    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-21T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-21T12:00:00-05:00" n="399"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J.C.S.</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Combined Chiefs of Staff Minutes</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-chapter-heading" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1943-08-21T13:00:00-04:00">August 21, 1943, 2:30 p.m.</date>
                </dateline>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">1. <hi rend="smallcaps">Conclusions of the Previous Meeting</hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The Combined Chiefs of Staff</hi>:—</p>
                <p>Accepted the conclusions of the 113th Meeting. The detailed record of the meeting
                    was also accepted, subject to minor amendments.<note n="2" xml:id="d399fn2">The
                        amendments referred to have been incorporated in the minutes of the 113th
                        Meeting of the Combined Chiefs of Staff as printed <hi rend="italic"
                            >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_905">p. 905</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">2. <hi rend="smallcaps">Progress Report to the President and Prime
                        Minister</hi>
                    <lb/> (<gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 319/1<note n="3" xml:id="d399fn3"
                        >“Progress Report to the President and Prime Minister”, August 21, 1943; not
                        printed. See fn. 4, below.</note>)</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The Combined Chiefs of Staff</hi>:—</p>
                <p>Approved <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 319/1, as amended in the course
                    of the discussion. (Amended version subsequently published as <gloss
                        target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 319/2.<note n="4" xml:id="d399fn4">“Progress
                        Report to the President and Prime Minister”; not printed. The text of this
                        report (which dealt with the war against Japan), as revised in the light of
                        decisions taken by the Combined Chiefs of Staff during their 115th Meeting,
                        August 23, 1943 (see <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_937">p.
                            937</ref>), was not circulated by the Secretaries of the Combined Chiefs
                        of Staff until August 27, 1943, after their return to Washington. The
                        subject matter covered in <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 319/2 and
                        annex <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi> thereto is contained also, and in very
                        similar language, in paragraphs 20–33, 35–40, and 42–45 of <gloss
                            target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 319/5, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_1125">p. 1125</ref>. Annex <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi> to
                            <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 319/2 is identical with the
                        appendix to <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 313, <hi rend="italic"
                            >post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_981">p. 981</ref>.</note>)</p>
                <pb facs="1035" n="921" xml:id="pg_921"/>
                <p rend="center">3. <hi rend="smallcaps">Southeast Asia Command</hi>
                    <lb/> (<gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 308,<note n="5" xml:id="d399fn5">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_968">p. 968</ref>.</note>
                        308/1,<note n="6" xml:id="d399fn6">“Southeast Asia Command”, August 21,
                        1943; not printed. See fn. 2 to the enclosure to <gloss target="#t_CCS1"
                            >C.C.S.</gloss> 308/3, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_1001">p. 1001</ref>.</note> 308/2<note n="7"
                        xml:id="d399fn7">“Southeast Asia Command”, August 21, 1943; not printed. See
                        fn. 3 to the enclosure to <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 308/3, <hi
                            rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1002">p.
                    1002</ref>.</note>)</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The Combined Chiefs of Staff</hi>:— <list>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">a</hi>.</label>
                        <item>Approved <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 308, excluding
                            paragraph 8.</item>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">b</hi>.</label>
                        <item>Approved the amendments to paragraphs 8 <hi rend="italic">a</hi> and
                                <hi rend="italic">b</hi> set forth in <gloss target="#t_CCS1"
                                >C.C.S.</gloss> 308/1.</item>
                        <label>
                            <hi rend="italic">c</hi>.</label>
                        <item>Approved the amendment to paragraph 8 <hi rend="italic">c</hi> set
                            forth in <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 308/2. (The amended
                            paper subsequently published as <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss>
                                308/3.<note n="8" xml:id="d399fn8">
                                <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1000">p.
                                1000</ref>.</note>)</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">4. <hi rend="smallcaps">Specific Operations in the Pacific and Far
                        East</hi> 1943–1944<lb/>(<gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 301,<note
                        n="9" xml:id="d399fn9">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_426">p. 426</ref>.</note>
                        301/1,<note n="10" xml:id="d399fn10">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_971">p. 971</ref>.</note>
                        301/2<note n="11" xml:id="d399fn11">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_993">p. 993</ref>.</note>)</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The Combined Chiefs of Staff</hi>:—</p>
                <p>Approved the new subparagraph eight (<hi rend="italic">i</hi>) “Air Route into
                    China”, set forth by the U.S. Chiefs of Staff in <gloss target="#t_CCS1"
                        >C.C.S.</gloss> 301/2.</p>
                <p rend="center">5. <hi rend="smallcaps">Supply Routes in Northeast India</hi>
                    <lb/> (<gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 325<note n="12" xml:id="d399fn12">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1003">p.
                    1003</ref>.</note>)</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The Combined Chiefs of Staff</hi>:—</p>
                <p>Approved the recommendations contained in the paper.</p>
                <p rend="center">6. <hi rend="smallcaps">Air Plan for the Defeat of Japan</hi>
                    <lb/> (<gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 323<note n="13" xml:id="d399fn13">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_995">p. 995</ref>.</note>)</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The Combined Chiefs of Staff</hi>:—</p>
                <p>Agreed that this paper should be referred to the Combined Staff Planners for
                    study and the submission of an appropriate report to the Combined Chiefs of
                    Staff not later than 15 September 1943.</p>
            </div>
